{{EngvarB|date=March 2017}} {{Use dmy dates|date=March 2017}} {{Context|date=February 2012}} {{Infobox university |name = Indian Institute of Nano Science & Technology |logo = |image_name = |caption = |established = |type = [[Research]] [[Institution]] |director = |city = [[Bangalore]] |state = [[Karnataka]] |country = [[India]] |campus = |students = |undergrad = |postgrad = |website = }}
''' Indian Institute of Nano Science & Technology ''' ('''IINSc''') is a research institution that teaches [[Nanotechnology|nano science and technology]]. It is located in [[Bangalore]], [[India]].
==History== Karnataka is home to many such initiatives..and for Indian Institute of Nano Science & Technology to support and develop nanotechnology and reap the benefit of technology. Nanotechnology in India has started to noticed and high potential, develop and get importance in both research and commercial value.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/bangalore/report_garden-city-one-step-closer-to-setting-up-nano-park_1644535 |title=Garden City one step closer to setting up Nano Park - Bangalore - DNA |publisher=Dnaindia.com |date= |accessdate=2012-07-17}}</ref>
In Karnataka research centres like Jawaharlal Nehru Centre for Advanced Scientific Research Centre, Indian Institute of Science and the National Centre for Biological Sciences are main research institutes which support the nano park initiative.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pharmabiz.com/NewsDetails.aspx?aid=67481&sid=1 |title=Karnataka govt to allocate separate budget for nanotech initiatives, EoI for Nano Park to be evaluated by Feb 20 |publisher=Pharmabiz.com |date= |accessdate=2012-07-17}}</ref>
The focus of the Indian Institute of Nano Science & Technology will be research and development of nano materials.<ref>{{cite web|author=Our Bureau |url=http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/industry-and-economy/article2817719.ece?ref=wl_opinion |title=Business Line : Industry & Economy News : Grants for firms working on nano products |publisher=Thehindubusinessline.com |date= |accessdate=2012-07-17}}</ref>
Nano Park is the first of its kind in India and supports the development of medical devices, diagnostic kits and pharmaceuticals.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/education/research/article2844709.ece |title=The IISc stamp on science research |publisher=Thehindu.com |accessdate=2013-11-02}}</ref>
===Campus=== Karnataka state government initiated to set Nano Park in Bangalore with estimated budget allocation of Rs. 150 Crores . The park spreads 25 acres of land and building at Tumakur Road Bangalore. The Park will be on similar lines of an Information Technology Park.
===Main building=== The infrastructure would include a science and technology business incubator which will nurture early stage entrepreneurial ventures based on nano science and technology. There will be laboratories and clean rooms that will prove conducive for nano research.
