'''''Into the Open''''', subtitled "New Paintings, Prints and Sculptures by Contemporary Black Artists", was an exhibition of art by black artists displayed at various venues in the [[United Kingdom]] in 1984.
This exhibition was the first major survey by a municipal gallery of contemporary work by [[black artists]] in Britain, and is considered one of the landmark exhibitions of the 1980s.<ref>Eddie Chambers, [https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=dYDoAwAAQBAJ&pg=PA113&dq=%22into+the+open%22+exhibition+black+artists&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0CCEQ6AEwAGoVChMI4PjDjrXdxwIVh9gaCh2mewRj#v=onepage&q=%22into%20the%20open%22%20exhibition%20black%20artists&f=false ''Black Artists in British Art: A History since the 1950s''], I.B. Tauris, 2014, p. 113. {{ISBN|1780762720}}.</ref> It was curated, at the invitation of [[Sheffield City Arts Department]], by two people closely involved with black artists in Britain: [[Pogus Caesar]] and [[Lubaina Himid]]. Their stated aim was to give an indication of the range and richness of art made by contemporary [[wikt:Afro-Caribbean|Afro Caribbean]] artists.
The ''Into the Open'' exhibition toured in the United Kingdom in 1984, appearing at three venues: the [[Mappin Art Gallery]] in [[Sheffield]] (4 August–9 September 1984), the [[Nottingham Castle#Nottingham Castle Museum|Castle Museum]] in [[Nottingham]] (16 September–21 October 1984), and the [[Newcastle Media Workshops]] in [[Newcastle-upon-Tyne]] (2–24 November 1984).<ref>Chambers (2014), note 20, pp. 255–56.</ref> It was organized by the Sheffield Arts Department and was subsidised by the [[Arts Council of Great Britain]].
==Artists in the exhibition== {{div col|colwidth=18em}} * [[Clement Bedeau]] * [[Sylbert Bolton]] * [[Sonia Boyce]] * [[Pogus Caesar]] * [[Eddie Chambers (writer and artist)|Eddie A. Chambers]] * [[Shakka Dedi]] * [[Uzo Egonu]] * [[Lubaina Himid]] * [[Gavin Jantjes]] * [[Claudette Johnson]] * [[Tam Joseph|Tom Joseph]] * [[Juginder Lamba]] * [[Bill Ming]] * [[Ossie Murray]] * [[Houria Niati]] * [[Benjamin Nhlanhla Nsusha]] * [[Pitika Ntuli|Pitika P. Ntuli]] * [[Keith Piper (artist)|Keith Piper]] * [[Richie Riley]] * [[Veronica Ryan]] * Jorge Santos {{div col end}}
