{{Infobox university school | name = School of Engineering | parent = [[RMIT University]] College of Science, Engineering and Health | image = | head_label = Executive Dean | head = Adrian Mouritz<ref>[http://www.rmit.edu.au/about/our-education/academic-schools/engineering/contact/people People]. School of Engineering, [[RMIT University]]. Retrieved 24 October 2017</ref> | campus = [[RMIT City|City]], Bundoora | affiliations = | website = [http://www.rmit.edu.au/about/our-education/academic-schools/engineering School of Engineering] }}
The '''RMIT School of Engineering''' is an [[Australia]]n [[tertiary education]] school within the College of Science Engineering and Health of [[RMIT University]]. It was created in 2016 from the former schools of [[RMIT School of Aerospace, Mechanical and Manufacturing Engineering|Aerospace, Mechanical and Manufacturing Engineering]], [[RMIT School of Civil, Environmental and Chemical Engineering|Civil, Environmental and Chemical Engineering]], [[RMIT School of Computer Science and Information Technology|Computer Science and Information Technology]] and [[RMIT School of Electrical and Computer Engineering|Electrical and Computer Engineering]].
